-# Programmatic access — mint/regenerate/revoke a personal-access JWT for the
-# Atlas API. Wrapped in a turbo-frame so AtlasTokensController can swap just
-# this card in place (reveal-once): the minted token lives only in the response
-# that reveals it, never in the session or a subsequent page load. `token` is
-# set only on the mint response; `notice` carries an inline status line.
= turbo_frame_tag :atlas_token do
  -# Orange left rail (.my-drs-card--api) flags this as the credential surface —
  -# the same warning tone as the Cancel affordance, signalling "handle with care".
  .my-drs-card.my-drs-card--api.bg-white.border.rounded-3.overflow-hidden.shadow-sm
    .my-drs-card__head.p-3
      %h5.mb-1
        %i.fa-solid.fa-terminal.text-secondary.me-2{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
        Programmatic access
      %p.small.text-muted.mb-0
        A personal access token for driving the Atlas API directly — from your own scripts or the command line, without signing in through a browser.
    .p-3
      - if notice.present?
        .alert.alert-info.py-2.px-3.small.mb-3{ role: 'status' }= notice

      - if token.present?
        .alert.alert-warning.py-2.px-3.small.d-flex.align-items-start.mb-3{ role: 'alert' }
          %i.fa-solid.fa-triangle-exclamation.me-2.mt-1{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
          %div
            %strong.d-block Copy this token now — it won't be shown again.
            Treat it like a password: it grants full access as you, and expires one week from now.
        .small.fw-semibold.text-muted.mb-1 Your access token
        .input-group.mb-3{ data: { controller: 'clipboard', 'clipboard-text-value': token } }
          %code.form-control.bg-body-tertiary.font-monospace.text-break.user-select-all{ style: 'height: auto; white-space: normal;' }= token
          %button.btn.btn-outline-secondary{ type: 'button', 'aria-label' => 'Copy access token', data: { action: 'clipboard#copy' } }
            %i.fa-regular.fa-copy.me-1{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
            %span{ data: { 'clipboard-target': 'label' } } Copy
        %p.small.text-muted.mb-1 Then use it as a bearer token — for example, export it for atlas_rb:
        %pre.bg-body-tertiary.border.rounded-2.p-2.small.mb-3
          %code= 'export ATLAS_JWT=<your token>'
        .d-flex.gap-2
          = button_to atlas_token_path, method: :post, params: { regenerate: true }, class: 'btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary', data: { turbo_confirm: 'Regenerate your token? The current one stops working immediately.' } do
            %i.fa-solid.fa-rotate.me-1{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
            Regenerate
          = button_to atlas_token_path, method: :delete, class: 'btn btn-sm btn-outline-danger', data: { turbo_confirm: 'Revoke all your access tokens? Any scripts using them stop working immediately.' } do
            %i.fa-solid.fa-ban.me-1{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
            Revoke all
      - else
        %p.small.text-muted.mb-3
          Generate a token to authenticate as yourself against the Atlas API. Tokens expire after one week; you can revoke them at any time.
        .d-flex.gap-2
          = button_to atlas_token_path, method: :post, class: 'btn btn-sm btn-primary' do
            %i.fa-solid.fa-key.me-1{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
            Generate token
          = button_to atlas_token_path, method: :delete, class: 'btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary', data: { turbo_confirm: 'Revoke all your access tokens? Any scripts using them stop working immediately.' } do
            %i.fa-solid.fa-ban.me-1{ 'aria-hidden' => 'true' }
            Revoke all
